@node Introduction

           HELLO AND WELCOME TO MY FIRST ASSEMBLY LANGUAGE PROGRAM.
              
           
What does it do.

   It tries to Play OctaMed Modules using a mixture of Assembly language
   routines and library calls.

   Great yet other Module Player and whats so good about this one then

   Err well.

             1 Its small compact size. 
             2 The author is so sad he's tested it on just about every
               Type of Octamed Module. 
             3 It makes loads of checks and informs the user if anything
               go's wrong (most of the time).
             4 Checks Fastmem loading/Playing and turns on/off 
               accordingly.
             5 The user has a choice of using the simple window displayed
               on opening or clicking on the more gadget for extra goodies.
             6 Its got a very simple user interface.         
               
                             

                         @{"BACK" link Main}
@endnode

@node Installation
                             
                        Taffys Player (Installing it). 

   Installing this program is very easy you should have no problems just
   drag the Taffys Player Icon wherever you wish it to go on your Hard Disk.
    

Librarys:

   All the Libraries you need should already be in your sys/libs Drawer
   on your hard disk.

   If not the program will tell you what version number you need
   heres a list anyway.  
 
               medplayer.library     v7.1    4  Channels
               octaplayer.library    v7.1    8  Channels
               octamixplayer.library v7.1    64 Channels 

               gadtools.library      v39
               asl.library           v40
               dos.library           v39    ;
               intuition.library     v40    ;
               
                         @{"BACK" link Main}    
@endnode

@node Features

                               WHAT WILL IT PLAY.

             Octamed Sound Studio Modules and other Octamed Module Types.
             
             MMD0 MMD1 MMD2 MMD3.   
               
            
             ..............Automatically Checks the Following.............
             
                          
             Fastmem Play on/off at loading. 
             
             Load Fastram check before loading.
             
             Does not rely on the MMD id for Module Replaying or loading.
             
             Automatically loads to Fastram if Chip to Small and turns on
             Fastmem Play.
                        
             
             ..............................................................
             
                               Main Features.
                               
             "PLAY" Plays the currently loaded Module
             
             "STOP" Stops the currently Playing Module
             
             "CONT" Continues the Module from current Position
             
             "MORE" Clicking on this gadget opens a window with
             
              Various options Detailed below.
                               
 
 
                                            
   Clicking on the "MORE" Gadget after you've loaded a supported Module

               Will open a window for the type of Module loaded.


           I.   @{"Four Channel Octamed Module Loaded." link FourChannel}
           II.  @{"Eight Channel Octamed Module Loaded." link EightChannel }
           III. @{"Mix mode (64) Channel Octamed Module Loaded." link sixtyfourChannel}
           IV.  @{"General Module Information displayed on every window." link General}
                     
                         @{"BACK" link Main}
@endnode
                  
@node  FourChannel                    

           ............Options for 4 Channel Octamed Module............  
                     
                          --Medplayer Library v7.1-- 
                           
                           

              "Fastmem Play"           Turns Fastmem Play on/off.                      
              "Reset MIDI"             Not available in this version.
              "LowPass Filter"         Turns low pass filter on/off.
                                       The Module Playing will override
                                       this setting if audio filtering
                                       is used by the Module.

              "Fast Memory Play        Change the size of the Fast memory
               Buffer Size"            Play buffer.
               
               
               
               
              "Apply Changes"          Affects all the changes made
                                       with the cycle gadgets.
                                       Divide's the buffer contents
                                       by four checks max min.
                                       Stops the Module if Playing
                                       calls library routine's required.
              
              "PLAY"       Plays the currently loaded Module.
             
              "STOP"       Stops the currently Playing Module.
             
              "CONT"       Continues the Module from current Position.
              
              "EJECT&EXIT" Stops/Ejects/Unloads Module
                           Frees Player Closes Player library.
                           
                           
        .......................PLEASE NOTE......................
        
                                    
  When Playing Module from first window after adjusting the above settings.  
              
              Filter on/off is Ignored 
                                     
              Lowpass Filter is always set off on first window.
              
              Any Buffer size changes or Fastmem Play state will
              remain as set by this window.
                               
                           
                         @{"BACK" link Main}
@endnode

@node  General
                          
                       General Module Attributes.
        
                          
              Module Size : Size of Module in Bytes. 
         
              Instruments : Number of Samples Synth sounds used.
          
              Num Blocks  : Number of Blocks used.
          
              Playing Seq : Number of Blocks in sequence.
        
              Module Type : File Type of Module loaded.
        
              Memory Type : Type of Memory used Chip or Fast.
        
        
Please note:-    Playing Sel is used instead of Playing Seq
                 in Modules with file type MMD2 and above.                  
                 Which is the number of Sequences Used.    
                 
                                           
                         @{"BACK" link Main}                     
@endnode

@node  EightChannel                    

           ............Options for 8 Channel Octamed Module............  
                     
                          --Octaplayer Library v7.1-- 
                           
                           

              "Fastmem Play"           Turns Fastmem Play on/off.                      
              "High Quality"           Turns high Quality mode on/off.
              "Low Pass Filter"        Turns lowpass filter on/off.
                                       The Module Playing will override
                                       this setting if audio filtering
                                       is used by the Module.

              "Fast Memory Play        Change the size of the Fast memory
               Buffer Size"            Play buffer.
               
               
               
               
              "Apply Changes"          Affects all the changes made
                                       with the cycle gadgets.
                                       Divide's the buffer contents
                                       by four checks max min.                                       
                                       Stops the Module if Playing
                                       calls library routine's required.
              
              "PLAY"       Plays the currently loaded Module.
             
              "STOP"       Stops the currently Playing Module.
             
              "CONT"       Continues the Module from current Position.
              
              "EJECT&EXIT" Stops/Ejects/Unloads Module
                           Frees Player Closes Player library.
                           
                           
        .......................PLEASE NOTE......................
        
                                    
  When Playing Module from first window after adjusting the above settings.  
              
              Filter on/off is Ignored 
                                     
              Lowpass Filter is always set off on first window.
              
              Any buffer size changes or Fastmem Play or High Quality mode
              state will remain as set by this window.
                               
                           
                         @{"BACK" link Main}
@endnode

@node  sixtyfourChannel                    

       ........Options for Mix Mode (64) Channel Octamed Module........  
                     
                         --Octamixplayer Library v7.1-- 
                           
                           

              "Set 14Bit Mode"          Turns 14Bit Play Mode on/off.                      
              "LowPass Filter"          Turns lowpass filter on/off.
                                        The Module Playing will override
                                        this setting if audio filtering
                                        is used by the Module.

              "Change MixBuffer         Change the size of the Mixing 
               Buffer Size"             Buffer.
               
              "Change Mixing frequency" Change the Output Mixing  
                                        frequency.

               
               
              "Apply Changes"           Affects all the changes made
                                        with the cycle gadgets.
                                        Divide's the buffer contents
                                        by four checks max min.                                       
                                        Stops the Module if Playing
                                        calls library routine's required.
              
              "PLAY"       Plays the currently loaded Module.
             
              "STOP"       Stops the currently Playing Module.
             
              "CONT"       Continues the Module from current Position.
              
              "EJECT&EXIT" Stops/Ejects/Unloads Module
                           Frees Player Closes Player library.
                           
                           
        .......................PLEASE NOTE......................
        
                                    
  When Playing Module from first window after adjusting the above settings.  
              
              Filter on/off is Ignored 
                                     
              Lowpass Filter is always set off on first window.
              
              Any buffer size changes or Fastmem Play or Mixing mode
              state will remain as set by this window.
                               
                           
                         @{"BACK" link Main}
@endnode
